{"lemma":"أَعْوَجَيْ","slug":"أَعْوَجَيْ","root":"ع.#.ج","root_slug":"ع-_-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ج","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30924"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"crooked, bent, twisted, distorted"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ع و ج (ʕ w j).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʔaʕ.wad͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30924","headword_ar":"اَعْوَجِىٌّ","root":"Ewj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"the rel. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) and applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"[single]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horse of those termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEowajiy~aAtu","text_ar":"الاَعْوَجِيَّاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain horse so called in relation to one named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", belonging to the Benoo-Hilál, (S, O, K,) a stallion than which there was none more celebrated among the Arabs, nor any that had a more numerous progeny: (S, O:) they were also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayolu","text_ar":"الخَيْلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEowajiy~apu","text_ar":"الاَعْوَجِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu A^aEowaja","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ اَعْوَجَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwjK","text_ar":"عُوجٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waqaAHu AlHaAfiri ↓ \n      A^aHowaY mina AlEuwji"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Brown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a blackish bay, of the progeny of Aawaj, hard in the hoof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino waladi","text_ar":"مِنْ وَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaja","text_ar":"اَعْوَجَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; using that form of pl. because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally an epithet. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","O","K","L"]}]}}